description: Alterations to roof. Replacement of modern ladders and mansafe system to pitched roofs. Instalation of new traditional metal handrails.  Alterations to windows. Installation of new access walkways. Full planning consent sought under application reference 3035/21. (Summary).
decision_conditions:
The works to which this consent relate shall be begun not later than the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.

Reason: In order to comply with Section 18 of the Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990 and to ensure that the Local Planning Authority retains the right to review unimplemented consents and to ensure their long-term future in accordance with Policy LP33 in the Council’s Local Plan.

building_details.building_ref: Snaresbrook Crown Court (existing building, no new buildings proposed).

waste_details.reason_for_no_provision: This does not form part of this project.
